  "title": "Product Specialist-Medical( Balestier, 5 days)",
  "description": "<p>Our client is seeking for a detail-oriented and service-driven Product Support Specialist to provide clinical and technical support to healthcare providers using our medical devices. This role is crucial in ensuring product adoption, satisfaction, and safe use in clinical settings.<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Provide on-site case support and technical guidance during surgical procedures</li><li>Train medical staff on the proper use and handling of medical devices</li><li>Assist in the setup and troubleshooting of equipment</li><li>Act as a liaison between the sales team and clinical users to ensure smooth communication</li><li>Document and report field feedback for product improvement</li><li>Maintain up-to-date knowledge of clinical applications and product updates</li><li>Support the sales team with product demos, workshops, and conferences</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong><br />• Diploma/Degree in Nursing, Biomedical Engineering, Life Sciences, or a related field<br />• Experience supporting operating theatres or clinical environments is an advantage<br />• Good communication and interpersonal skills<br />• Strong technical aptitude and willingness to learn<br />• Able to work independently and manage field-based duties<br />• Willing to travel locally; must possess own transport<br /><br /><strong>Perks & Benefits</strong><br />• Competitive starting salary<br />• Case & transport allowance (Monthly)• Quarterly performance bonus and AWS<br />• Professional Development – Opportunities for career growth, training, and career development<br />• Medical benefits<br /><br />**We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.<br />Your Profile will be kept in our database for more career opportunities.<br />We wish you all the best in your job search.<br /><br />EA personnel: Ong Ping Tiong<br />EA personnel Reg No: R25127323EA <br />License No: 24C2562 </p>",
